This paper involves the use of phone sensors to collect data related to gait changes during drinking episodes, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the study involves the use of an artificial neural network to analyze the collected data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves the use of sensors and data collection techniques, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the study involves the analysis of data related to alcohol consumption, which could fall under the category of other (cs.OH).
